text: "Jumper" is a 1998 song by American rock band Third Eye Blind. It is the fifth and final single from their debut studio album Third Eye Blind. It went to number 5 in the United States and number 10 in Canada. It deals with suicide in the LGBT community. ==Track listings and formats== * CD, cassette, and 7-inch # "Jumper" (radio edit) – 4:06 # "Graduate" (remix) – 3:26 == References == Category:1998 songs Category:Alternative rock songs Category:Power pop songs Category:LGBT songs Category:Third Eye Blind songs
